title: V14 (#58)
message:
V14 (#58)

* Added checkboxes for Vitamin B12 and Vitamin D.

* Vitamins are not counted in the daily total servings.

* Refactored the usage of some hardcoded values

* Removed an unused method

* Updated version to 14

* Added translations for Vitamin B12 and Vitamin D. Removed unnecessary copies of the food_quantities integer-array from the translation files.

* Moved the call to dismiss the notification from MainActivity's onCreate to onResume. In onCreate, the notification was not being dismissed if the app was running in the background.

* greek translation fixes (#57)

* greek translation fixes

* Update strings.xml

* Added icons for Vitamin B12 and Vitamin D

* Replaced TODO with comment

* Replaced the Vitamin D icon with a filled in sun

* Added a divider to inform users that checking vitamins does not update the daily servings count

* Added translations for vitamins dialog text.

* Added a null check for the result of getFoodByName when restoring from backup files

* Updated the Spanish translation

* Increase versionCode

title: Updated pull_database.sh to work without requiring root access. The script only…
message: Updated pull_database.sh to work without requiring root access. The script only works with debug builds of the app.

title: V13.1 (#56)
message:
V13.1 (#56)

* German: Translate "tablespoon" with "Esslöffel"

See: https://dict.leo.org/englisch-deutsch/tablespoon

* Improve German translation

- Fixes typos.
- Fixes misleading/wrong translations.
- Improves punctuation.
- Improves understandability.
- Harmonizes form of address ("du" instead of "Sie").

* Fixed minor bug where notification is not dismissed unless you open the app by tapping the notification.

* Updated version to 13.1

* Updated README.md

title: V13 (#53)
message:
V13 (#53)

* Updated the app version to v13.

* Tapping on a date in the FoodHistoryActivity now takes the user to that date.

* Added button to FoodInfoActivity that allows the user to change between Imperial and Metric units. This implementation does not work with translations, so it will need to be refactored.

* Split the serving size strings into an unformatted string-array and two string-arrays for Imperial and Metric units.

* Refactored to support Spanish translation. Updating the rest of the translations should be fairly straightforward.

* Updated the Bulgarian translation

* Updated the German translation

* Updated the Greek translation

* Updated the French translation

* Small changes to English strings

* Startup performance improvement. No longer loading and caching all FoodInfo on startup. Only food icons are loaded initially since they are used on the first screen the user sees. If the user taps into FoodInfoActivity, then the rest of the data is loaded and cached.

* Added a comment to initServingSizesForFood

* Moved the change units button underneath the "Serving Sizes" label. This prevents the label and button from being hidden with long translations.

* Don't show the change units button when displaying info for exercise

* Added missing translations that were preventing the apk from being built

* Replaced all German metric volume units with metric weight units from the book

* Reverted MPAndroidChart to 2.1.6. Updating to 2.2.5 has made MPAndroidChart the main source of crashes in the app.

* The user can now jump to a date from the ServingsHistoryActivity

* Added Greek and Bulgarian translations for grams. Removed some trailing commas in the strings files.

* Fixed display bug where the tops of the chart labels were being cut off.

* User can now only jump to a specific date if they are viewing the daily servings history. LoadServingsHistoryTask now returns a LoadServingsHistoryCompleteEvent so extra data can be passed with the complete event.

* Updated README.md

* Extracted the "%d out of %d" string and added translations for it.

* Fixed bug where days without servings were not included in the trend calculation. Now, those missing days are counted as 0 servings. This provides a more accurate trend for users who are more sporadic in their use of the app.

message: Fixed bug in getServingsOfFoodInMonth. Very rare bug that I would have only found today, December 31st. The problem was that adding 1 month to Oct 31 changed the date to Nov 30, but adding 1 month to Nov 30 changed the date to Dec 30 and not Dec 31 like I was expecting it to. I fixed the bug by only looking at the year and month properties of the calendar as that is all I was interested in anyways.
